Root-cause (axe flake): a FAIL appeared only on the FIRST light-theme scan. Not a real AA defect — axe was sampling mid-transition: flipping data-theme via setAttribute animates .tab-label color through a low-contrast mid-gray over 160ms (--motion-fast). A normally-loaded card (theme pre-applied by the head anti-flash script) shows NO transition; reduced-motion shows none; re-setting the same theme shows none. Ruled out with a 90-scan loop = 0 failures once transitions are zeroed. localStorage-set-then-navigate was rejected as the fix: it reads stale-by-one under the active SW in this harness (verified). Final approach: setAttribute (reliable, shell-suite pattern) + reducedMotion (deterministic, settled frame).
Command: node scripts/build-data.mjs ; node tests/content.spec.mjs ; node tests/shell.spec.mjs ; + 90x standalone axe stability loop.
