  - Card AA contrast is verified on a SETTLED frame (theme applied at load / reduced-motion). If the Evaluator flips theme via setAttribute on a live card and runs axe within the 160ms color transition, axe may report a transient color-contrast on .tab-label. This is the theme-toggle animation, not the card's steady state; scan after load in each theme (or under reduced-motion), matching the Sprint-001 shell-suite pattern. The transient is a Sprint-001 chrome property, exempt under prefers-reduced-motion, left unchanged to keep the five existing screens identical.
